{
  "texts": [
    "Building on these foundations, the introduction of high-quality datasets (Chen et al., 2023a; Zhao et al., 2023; Wang et al., 2023b; Li et al., 2023c) for different training stages (e.g., multimodal alignment, instruction tuning, preference alignment) has enabled LVLMs to achieve strong performance across diverse real-world scenarios.",
    "Despite effectively leveraging pretrained vision and language components, the pipeline architecture can accumulate errors across modules.",
    "No systematic investigation has yet been conducted to attribute model failures to specific components, limiting interpretability and understanding of modality alignment.",
    "Evaluation and Benchmarking.",
    "Recent years have witnessed the emergence of numerous benchmarks for evaluating LVLM capabilities across cognitive and perceptual dimensions (Liang et al., 2024; Fu et al., 2024b,a; Liu et al., 2024d; Yu et al., 2024; Li et al., 2023a; Lee et al., 2024; Zhang et al., 2025), assessing various aspects including reasoning skills, understanding abilities, and inherent knowledge."
  ]
}